{"title_page": "South African National Parks", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2019}}\n{{short description|The body responsible for managing South Africa's national parks.}}\n{{Infobox government agency\n|agency_name   = South African National Parks\n|nativename    =\n|nativename_a  = \n|nativename_r  = \n|logo          = SANParks logo.svg\n|logo_width    = 200px\n|logo_caption  = \n|seal          = \n|seal_width    = \n|seal_caption  = \n|picture       = \n|picture_width = \n|picture_caption = \n|formed        = 1926\n|jurisdiction  = [[Government of South Africa]]\n|headquarters  = 643 Leyds Street, Muckleneuk, [[Pretoria]]\n|coordinates   = {{coord|25|45|59|S|28|12|8|E|type:landmark_region:ZA|display=inline}}\n|employees     = 4,027 (permanent)<br>1,405 (temporary)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sanparks.org/assets/docs/general/annual-report-2016.pdf |title=South African National Parks Annual Report 2015/16 |publisher=South African National Parks |isbn=978-0-621-44439-1 |format=PDF |page=125 |accessdate=23 August 2017}}</ref>\n|budget        = [[South African rand|R]]1,815,542<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sanparks.org/assets/docs/general/annual-report-2016.pdf |title=South African National Parks Annual Report 2015/16 |publisher=South African National Parks |isbn=978-0-621-44439-1 |format=PDF |page=140 |accessdate=23 August 2017}}</ref>\n|minister1_name  = [[Edna Molewa|B E E (Edna) Molewa]]\n|minister1_pfo   = [[Minister of Water and Environmental Affairs (South Africa)|Minister of Water and Environmental Affairs]]\n|chief1_name     = Joanne Yawitch\n|chief1_position = [[Chairman|Chairperson of the Board]]\n|chief2_name     = Fundisile Mketeni \n|chief2_position = CEO\n|agency_type   =\n|parent_agency = [[Department of Environmental Affairs (South Africa)|Department of Environmental Affairs]]\n|keydocument1=National Parks Act, 1976\n|keydocument2=National Environmental Management: Protected Areas Act, 2003\n|website       = [http://www.sanparks.org/ www.sanparks.org]\n|footnotes     = \n|map       = \n|map_width = \n|map_caption = \n|chief3_name=|chief3_position=|chief4_name=|chief4_position=|chief5_name=|chief5_position=|chief6_name=|chief6_position=|chief7_name=|chief7_position=|chief8_name=|chief8_position=|chief9_name=|chief9_position=|parent_department=}}\n'''South African National Parks''' (SANParks) is the body responsible for managing South Africa's [[national park]]s. SANParks was formed in 1926, and currently manages 19 parks consisting of  {{convert|3751113|ha|km2}},<ref>{{cite web |last1=South Africa National Parks |title=Brief History |url=https://www.sanparks.org/about/history.php |website=SANParks |accessdate=19 June 2019}}</ref> over 3% of the total area of South Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sanparks.org/assets/docs/general/annual-report-2016.pdf |title=South African National Parks Annual Report 2015/16 |publisher=South African National Parks |isbn=978-0-621-44439-1 |format=PDF |page=6 |accessdate=26 August 2017}}</ref>{{efn|[[Groenkloof Nature Reserve|Groenkloof]] and Graspan/Vaalbos are declared national parks in legislation but are not operationally functional national parks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sanparks.org/assets/docs/general/annual-report-2016.pdf |title=South African National Parks Annual Report 2015/16 |publisher=South African National Parks |isbn=978-0-621-44439-1 |format=PDF |page=15 |accessdate=26 August 2017}}</ref>}}\n\nMany parks offer a variety of accommodations. The best known park is [[Kruger National Park]], which is also the oldest (proclaimed in 1898), and the largest, at nearly {{convert|2000000|ha|km2}}. Kruger National Park and [[Table Mountain National Park]] are two of South Africa's most visited tourist attractions.\n\nThough not designated as National Parks, other [[Protected areas of South Africa|protected areas]] exist, such as game and nature reserves.\n\n==List of parks administered by SANParks==\nThe following are designated as National Parks of South Africa:<ref name=SANPARKS-about>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanparks.org/about|title=About Us: Nature's Best! |publisher=South African National Parks|accessdate=22 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" \n!scope=\"col\" | Name\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Photo\n!scope=\"col\" | Location\n!scope=\"col\" |Date established\n!scope=\"col\" data-sort-type=\"number\"|Area\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Addo Elephant National Park]]\n|[[File:Addo Elephant National Park-001.jpg|160px]]\n|[[Eastern Cape]]<br/><small>{{coord|-33.26|25.44}}</small>\n|{{dts|1931}}\n|{{convert|1642|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} \n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Agulhas National Park]]\n|[[File:AgulhasLighthouse.jpg|160px]]\n|[[Western Cape]]<br/><small>{{coord|-34.50|20.00}}</small>\n|{{dts|14 September 1998}}\n|{{convert|56.9|km2|abbr=on}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Ai-Ais/Richtersveld Transfrontier Park]]<br>{{spaces|5}}[[Richtersveld National Park]] (South Africa)<br>{{spaces|5}}[[Ai-Ais Hot Springs]] (Namibia)\n|[[File:Fish River Canyon Namibia.jpg|160px]]\n|[[Northern Cape]]<br/><small>{{coord|-28.053889|17.034722}}</small>\n|{{dts|2003}}<br>{{dts|1991}}<br>{{dts|1968}}\n|{{convert|5920|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.peaceparks.org/tfca.php?pid=19&mid=1001 |title=/Ai /Ais-Richtersveld Transfrontier Park |publisher=Peace Parks Foundation |date=21 April 2017 |accessdate=22 August 2017}}</ref><br>{{convert|1624|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref name=SANPARKS-about/><br>{{convert|4611|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.met.gov.na/national-parks/-ai-ais-hot-springs-game-park/212/ |publisher=Ministry of Environment and Tourism Namibia |title=/Ai-/Ais Hot Springs Game Park |accessdate=25 August 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Augrabies Falls National Park]]\n|[[File:Augrabie, Waterfalls, South Africa.jpg|160px]]\n|[[Northern Cape]]<br/><small>{{coord|-28.591111|20.338333}}</small>\n|{{dts|1966}}\n|{{convert|417|km2|sqmi|abbr=