two of South Africa's most visited tourist attractions.\n\nThough not designated as National Parks, other [[Protected areas of South Africa|protected areas]] exist, such as game and nature reserves.\n\n==List of parks administered by SANParks==\nThe following are designated as National Parks of South Africa:<ref name=SANPARKS-about>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanparks.org/about|title=About Us: Nature's Best! |publisher=South African National Parks|accessdate=22 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" \n!scope=\"col\" | Name\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Photo\n!scope=\"col\" | Location\n!scope=\"col\" |Date established\n!scope=\"col\" data-sort-type=\"number\"|Area\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Addo Elephant National Park]]\n|[[File:Addo Elephant National Park-001.jpg|160px]]\n|[[Eastern Cape]]<br/><small>{{coord|-33.26|25.44}}</small>\n|{{dts|1931}}\n|{{convert|1642|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} \n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Agulhas National Park]]\n|[[File:AgulhasLighthouse.jpg|160px]]\n|[[Western Cape]]<br/><small>{{coord|-34.50|20.00}}</small>\n|{{dts|14 September 1998}}\n|{{convert|56.9|km2|abbr=on}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Ai-Ais/Richtersveld Transfrontier Park]]<br>{{spaces|5}}[[Richtersveld National Park]] (South Africa)<br>{{spaces|5}}[[Ai-Ais Hot Springs]] (Namibia)\n|[[File:Fish River Canyon Namibia.jpg|160px]]\n|[[Northern Cape]]<br/><small>{{coord|-28.053889|17.034722}}</small>\n|{{dts|2003}}<br>{{dts|1991}}<br>{{dts|1968}}\n|{{convert|5920|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.peaceparks.org/tfca.php?pid=19&mid=1001 |title=/Ai /Ais-Richtersveld Transfrontier Park |publisher=Peace Parks Foundation |date=21 April 2017 |accessdate=22 August 2017}}</ref><br>{{convert|1624|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref name=SANPARKS-about/><br>{{convert|4611|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.met.gov.na/national-parks/-ai-ais-hot-springs-game-park/212/ |publisher=Ministry of Environment and Tourism Namibia |title=/Ai-/Ais Hot Springs Game 